 {"id":"bd-16tb","title":"Implement invariant checking functions","description":"## Overview

Implement functions that verify all region tree invariants, to be called after each operation in property tests.

## Invariant Checker Structure

```rust
/// Checks all region tree invariants.
/// 
/// This is called after every operation in property tests to verify
/// the tree remains in a valid state.
/// 
/// # Panics
/// 
/// Panics with a descriptive message if any invariant is violated.
pub fn assert_all_invariants(tree: &RegionTree) {
    assert_no_orphan_tasks(tree);
    assert_valid_tree_structure(tree);
    assert_child_tracking_consistent(tree);
    assert_unique_ids(tree);
    assert_cancel_propagation(tree);
    assert_close_ordering(tree);
    assert_budget_inheritance(tree);
}
```

## Individual Invariant Checks

### Invariant 1: No Orphan Tasks
```rust
fn assert_no_orphan_tasks(tree: &RegionTree) {
    for task in tree.all_tasks() {
        let region_id = task.region_id();
        assert\!(
            tree.region_exists(region_id),
            "Task {:?} references non-existent region {:?}",
            task.id(),
            region_id
        );

        let region = tree.get_region(region_id).unwrap();
        assert\!(
            region.contains_task(task.id()),
            "Task {:?} claims region {:?} but region doesn't list it",
            task.id(),
            region_id
        );
    }
}
```

### Invariant 2: Valid Tree Structure
```rust
fn assert_valid_tree_structure(tree: &RegionTree) {
    // Check single root
    let roots: Vec<_> = tree.regions()
        .filter(|r| r.parent().is_none())
        .collect();
    assert_eq\!(roots.len(), 1, "Expected exactly one root, found {:?}", roots);

    // Check no cycles via DFS
    let mut visited = HashSet::new();
    let mut stack = vec\![(tree.root_id(), HashSet::new())];

    while let Some((id, mut ancestors)) = stack.pop() {
        assert\!(
            \!ancestors.contains(&id),
            "Cycle detected: region {:?} is its own ancestor",
            id
        );

        if visited.insert(id) {
            ancestors.insert(id);
            let region = tree.get_region(id).unwrap();
            for child_id in region.children() {
                stack.push((*child_id, ancestors.clone()));
            }
        }
    }

    // Check all regions reachable from root
    assert_eq\!(
        visited.len(),
        tree.region_count(),
        "Some regions not reachable from root"
    );
}
```

### Invariant 3: Child Tracking Consistent
```rust
fn assert_child_tracking_consistent(tree: &RegionTree) {
    for region in tree.regions() {
        // Check each child points back to this parent
        for child_id in region.children() {
            let child = tree.get_region(*child_id)
                .expect("Child region doesn't exist");
            assert_eq\!(
                child.parent(),
                Some(region.id()),
                "Child {:?} has wrong parent: expected {:?}, got {:?}",
                child_id,
                region.id(),
                child.parent()
            );
        }

        // Check parent lists this as child
        if let Some(parent_id) = region.parent() {
            let parent = tree.get_region(parent_id)
                .expect("Parent region doesn't exist");
            assert\!(
                parent.children().contains(&region.id()),
                "Region {:?} has parent {:?} but parent doesn't list it as child",
                region.id(),
                parent_id
            );
        }
    }
}
```

### Invariant 4: Unique IDs
```rust
fn assert_unique_ids(tree: &RegionTree) {
    let mut region_ids = HashSet::new();
    for region in tree.regions() {
        assert\!(
            region_ids.insert(region.id()),
            "Duplicate region ID: {:?}",
            region.id()
        );
    }

    let mut task_ids = HashSet::new();
    for task in tree.all_tasks() {
        assert\!(
            task_ids.insert(task.id()),
            "Duplicate task ID: {:?}",
            task.id()
        );
    }
}
```

### Invariant 5: Cancel Propagation
```rust
fn assert_cancel_propagation(tree: &RegionTree) {
    for region in tree.regions() {
        if region.is_cancelled() {
            // All descendants must also be cancelled
            for descendant_id in tree.descendants(region.id()) {
                let descendant = tree.get_region(descendant_id).unwrap();
                assert\!(
                    descendant.is_cancelled(),
                    "Region {:?} is cancelled but descendant {:?} is not",
                    region.id(),
                    descendant_id
                );
            }
        }
    }
}
```

